The paper deals with the construction of additive spanners, which are a type of graph structure commonly studied in computer science. The paper uses techniques from graph theory and algorithm design, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial methods, which are relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, as spanners are commonly used in the analysis of network structures.
